<br>
Tripple amount of Qeynos guards<br>
(all serve Kane Bayle - evil brother)<br>
This is a fact and very conerning. Since the srhine of Bertoxxulous inthe Catacombs is VERY big and filled up with strong and mighty evil persons, I assume that the evil forces would actually have not the slightest problem taking over the Lead in Qeynos.<br>
This is a very concerning danger. I can only think that the reason they didn't take over the city yet, is because they are waiting for another Event to happen or a certain confirmation.<br>
But Qeynos needs to be protected. Immediately and with powerful armies.<br>
We also should send a spy frequently down there as well as our informants through the city.<br>
<br>
Servant of Mayong Mistmoore found wandering<br>
within Lfay, asking questions about FV's<br>
arrival home and reporting back to Mayong<br>
Mayong has his part in this. No doubt. He and Lanys seem to be allied and with the power of Mayong Mistmoore, Lanys will have a full army ready at her hands to bring Firiona in danger.<br>
<br>
Carson Mcabe, once HH Lt, now seaker of <br>
BB Hammer, discovered in The Hole<br>
He seems to have allied with the Bloodsabres. He also takes place in many stories and his signs are sprad all over Norrath. He is after the hammer which we also need to not let happen. Carson is a weapon dealer and a Bloodsabre ally!<br>
<br>
I am also wondering about Neriak. It seems as if theres a division of sorts amidst royalty. The Queen doesn't approve of how the King hunts Lanys. Teir'Dal civil war in the making perhaps? We do know that the King and the Queen seemingly are opposing each other now. <br>
<br>
Heres a surmising theory to the aforementioned. What if the King wants to dispose his wife? What if Lanys is secretly his lover and to become the new king? How else would she keep &quot;getting away&quot; all the time? Anyone notice the heavy influence of Bertoxxulous thats slowly appearing in Neriak starting with the X'lottl household and the other items of note? Lanys also captured Ashteth, the seer of Innoruuk who is gifted with visions of Innoruuk's will.<br>
<br>
lvl50+ spawns in Kithicor during the daylight hours.<br>
We have seen them. We have names and we have screenshots.<br>
They are VERY powerful. The question is, what do they do there? Are they on the Kings side or on the Queens? Or are they a party on their own? Noone has been able to find any explenation of this yet. But for sure it is concerning. My guess is that they are allied with the King since the Queen seems to represent the &quot;good&quot; side of Neriak (if there is one). The King allied with Lanys as m^rumors say, the Queen is hurt. Since the DE's in Kithicor are KOS to everyone, they must be evil. If they would be on the Queens side, I suppose that at least other DE's would be able to at least talk to them or not be attacked. <br>
<br>
Infos about the DEs in Kithicor:<br>
Tasi V'Ghera with pet<br>
Brigadier G'Tau<br>
Advisor C'Zatl<br>
Loltos V'Ghera with pet<br>
Coercer Q'Ioul<br>
Adjudant D'Kan<br>
War Priestess T'Zau<br>
<br>
Coordinates: pos695 pos2416<br>
<br>
<br>
Usually plain stone structure by the<br>
named Treant in NK, covered in signs of <br>
Trakanon.<br>
Its not just a sign of Trakanon. Its the signs that appear EVERYWHERE. We have not been able to find an explenation of the sign yet either. But we suppose its a strong sign with an important meaning. Maybe used to teleport. <br>
<br>
Bertoxxulous markings found near the<br>
X'lottl mansion (in Neriak).<br>
This goes in the same example as the treants rock signs. I suppose.<br>
<br>
Tayla Ironforge, which has a deep part in the story was originally a friend of Ton Firepride. Ton helped Tayla move, or more to the point introduced her to Carson who in fact did the move. Again note all the smugglers and Carson's dark elf contact to them outside the gates. Carson moved her to Neriak where she ended up in the maidens fancy where she was picked up by a &quot;powerful merchant&quot;.<br>
<br>
Here is our link. Mare X'lottl. SHE was in the Maidens Fancy where Tayla was. The inkeep THREW the game of Kings Court on purpose. Why? Think about what we know about House X'lottl. The &quot;powerfull merchant&quot; was none other then the Haggle Baron of Cabalis. Tayla Ironforge is STILL there now.<br>
<br>
<br>
The gnomes!<br>
The gnome with Edril's amulet IS in the Hole. He has actually and physically been seen. His name is Nortlav the Scalekeeper. There have been seen gnomes in the plane of hate, several! A gnome has been seen at the release of the Plague in the Lands of Karana. Also have been seen gnome messengers around.<br>
Those gnomes SEEM to not have allied with anyone and just be the good people. but this is WRONG!<br>
Those gnomes seem to in fact be part of this. They are in the background and hardly show up, but if they do, they certainly are involved in very important happenings.<br>
We must send a gnome spy in the City of Ak'Anon and have him find out more. Best would be a gnome necromancer.<br>
<br>
There are those half gods (ooc GMs) appearing and giving quests or giving small bits of information.<br>
So we have that Dark Elf appearing at the entrance of Befallen giving the following informations to a helper within the discussion:<br>
- The source of the Plague is &quot;some gods and I&quot;<br>
- being asked about an attack on Qeynos this eve  he answered &quot;Not this Eve&quot;. Saying this he still agreed that there WILL be an attak on Qeynos.<br>
- There is &quot;a lot more to Innoruuk in Plane of Hate than just the simple diety&quot;.<br>
-  and that &quot;Bertoxxulous is just a Servant of Innoruuk&quot;<br>
<br>
So this means 3 things.<br>
Qeynos WILL be attacked!<br>
We need to gather some forces and finally REALLY clear the plane of hate tosee what is going on there. This is also because (3rd thing we know) Bertoxxulous is a servant to Innoruuk. If this is so, then Innoruuk, again, is our true enemy. We need to find out more about this as much as (in this case) about the TIer'Dal and Dark Elfes in General. Neriak and Kithicor again take a more and more important position in this. We must keep Innoruuk and Neriak in mind, besides Qeynos and Bertoxxulous.<br>
<br>
The other GM event I heared of lately (thanks Brax) doesn't give new information but certainly CONFIRMS!<br>
and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  if anyone still doubts in all this after the words of this GM, then you certainly are not just ignorant, but also completely blind!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
There was a GM talking about a SK in Befallen that should be killed to help Innoruuk. Here is the text.<br>
GM: &quot;Hail Trkahon. Are<br>
you a loyal servant of Innoruuk and do you want to join the forces of<br>
hate?&quot;.<br>
Brax's Guildmate: &quot;Sure I am on your side.&quot;<br>
GM: &quot;Then go to a befallen state and seek out a shadowknight traitor.<br>
He posesses a key. Bring me his key to prove your loyalty.&quot;<br>
Brax's Guildmate: &quot;I shal do so now and shatter our enemy.&quot;<br>
GM: &quot;Very well may hate be your guide.&quot;<br>
<br>
He goes, kills the SK and brings the Key back to the gate of Neriak: &quot;Hail M'Lord. The traitor was no match for me as hate was with me, here<br>
is the key you asked for.&quot;<br>
GM: &quot;Very good Trkahon, you have proven yourself to our forces. Take this<br>
gift as a sign.&quot;<br>
GM gives him a &quot;Enchanted Teir'Dal Bastard Sword&quot; (2HS 23/45 str +7).<br>
Brax's Guildmate: &quot;Thank you M'Lord. If you ever again need my skills call and I will be<br>
at your service.&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  GM: &quot;Watch for the sign, our forces are gathering and within the next month<br>
