Then the patch message of the 30th May.<br>
There is not much to say about it all then, they are preparing the war with this patch. The first war, supposedly in Greater Faydark (but also Qeynos and Kithicor could be involved since the situation there is also very critical), will take place in my opinion IN THE WEEK AFTER THE PATCH!<br>
I will have to talk to our forces on the next meeting. We NEED to really place our forces during this week. We will NOT have time to start the whole teleport engine when this has begun. We will have to teleport, but we will NOT be able to teleport around 500 people around!<br>
/ooc out<br>
<br>
Lanys is seeking the Malevolence.<br>
She is out there looking for it knowing she wil not defeat Firiona without it. Do not help her with it. If she comes to you and asks you for help, spit in her face and go away. Report where you have seen her! <br>
<br>
There is a lady in Qeynos...Nerissa Clothspinner...her sister left her in the care of Kane Bayle. Has anyone talked to her or seen her recently?? I dont remember seeing her my last trip to Qeynos which is odd because she is usually everywhere. Perhaps she has something to say....perhaps not. But it does seem odd that her sister is located in the Karanas and also she is a ward of Kane Bayle yet knows nothing of his evil nature.<br>
The BLoodsabres want her sister Milea dead. They are afraid that Nerissa or Milea will talk and be a danger for the shrine of bertoxxulous. Maybe they both are not fleeing from the assassins. Namely Rithur Fullome is asking to get her killed. GO to the shrine to learn more about it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Three named undead gnolls, Triza the Dead, Gezra the Dead, and Braza the Dead up and started wandering around in south Karana. I have no explenation of this so far but the fear that this may be the first sign of the union between Bertoxxulous and Innoruuk.<br>
Gnolls are mostly Bloodsabres, followers of Bertoxxulous (note: INFECTED Paw), and who is the Lord of the death? Innoruuk. Very concerning thought! Maybe this is one of the kind we have to expect to fight in the Karanas in the war.<br>
<br>
<br>
The shrine of Bertoxxulous is not just very big, it is also filled up with many dozens of very strong followers of Bertoxxulous. Down there you find the Necromancer Guild, the Shadowknight Guild, the Enchanter Guild as well as numerous people that seem to be high priests of Bertoxxulous that seem not to directly belong to one of the Guilds. This is WAY bigger and stronger than the shrine used to be!<br>
Also what the followers in there have to say makes you think.<br>
Garuc Anehm says 'Kane Bayle and the leaders of this shrine all wish to overthrow the rule of Antonius Bayle. He, for power, and we for the glory of Bertoxxulous. From this city, our diseased lord shall appear and tread across the land spitting death from his mouth and deforming the land. His glory shall be eternal! <br>
<br>
<br>
Another thing we completely ignored so far is the fact that many hints point towards... Kunark. Obviously the Chardokian Royal Family as well as the City of Cabilis is well involved in all this. Rumors say that in fact Firiona Vie has been kidnapped by Iksars. We need to send an investigation team over to Kunark to check the city of Cabilis, the Field of BOne as well as Trakanons Teeth.<br>
Has anone gotten any informations from Cabilis? We need to inspect this further. After all was Firiona suposedly kidnapped by Iksars from Cabilis!<br>
<br>
<br>
This following talk has been mentioned several times, but just now I got aware of its importance:<br>
[Mon May 14 21:51:34 2001] You say, 'What has bertoxxulous released on Norrath?'<br>
[Mon May 14 21:51:34 2001] Roesager Thusten says 'Bertoxxulous is a vile creature who rules the Plane of Disease. His filthy followers are spreading their stain across all of Norrath. We fear they are already here in Qeynos. <br>
