Today, on the Zebuxoruk server their was an exciting GM event that took place. I remember reading about Fironia Vie's return on another server, so when I heard she was seen I immediately investigated it. I followed a group of around 20-30 people who were all following Fironia Vie until she stopped and talked to a unicorn. She then led the grop to the faerie village where she gave four stones to four specially selected people who took on the surnames based on the elemental stone they were given (rock, fire, earth, and water) I have no idea what this did to the recipients, but a little there afterward Fironia Vie performed a 'ritual' which eventually resulted in appearance by Tunare (I have some cool screens of the event too.)<br>
<br>
Afterward, people continued to be amazed and awed, but after time several negative messages regaurding the approach of something ecil were displayed, and at the climax of it all Cazic Thule, the Faceless himself appeared. At the time I was only a level 12 paladin so I didn't have a prayer against him. I found this out the hard way after bashing him once, he hit for 680 damage. The unicorn fought as well, but it got cursed and I think died later on. Afterwards I spent a while trying to get my corpse.<br>
<br>
By the time I reached the faerie village it appeared that there was just some closing dialogue to be said, and since I had mostly just been observing I left and returned to Felwithe, where a certain character (I forgot his name but it started with an R) was congratulated by what I believe was an NPC general of a sort. It will be cool when I can actually participate in these events instead of just watching.<br>
<br>
I took some screenshots of the event you should be able to see here as well.<br>
